description: Something powerful just took out Captain Stupendous, leaving Fusion to find out just what kind of creature is stalking the city streets. Luckily, she has Brooder and Grasshopper to help her. But what happens when she finds herself--alone--facing this fearsome foe? What hope does she have in confronting a creature that knocked Captain Stupendous out with a single blow? And what will she do when she finds herself at odds with none other than Brooder? The answers are inside Fusion #3!

Where are all the villains, you ask? Unfortunately for Fusion, they're arriving by the boatload in this issue! In fact, there are too many villains for a regular issue, so this issue is GIANT-SIZED! Who is killing heroes, and what is their agenda? How do you stop someone who can control your mind? What's the best way to stop a speedster? The answers are inside Fusion #4!
HAL JORDAN and KILOWOG find adventure on a new planet! RAZER is almost kidnapped by a SPIDER GUILD bounty hunter! AYA, the ship’s computer, takes her new robot body for a spin!
name: Bounty Hunter

description: This Xeric Award-winning graphic travelogue takes readers on an offbeat globetrotting adventure, including a cave expedition in Thailand, a stint as extras in a Singaporean soap opera, and a train ride through war-torn Serbia.

volume.name: A Few Perfect Hours and Other Stories from Southeast Asia and Central Europe

description: Graham Annable's follow up to his Harvey-nominated graphic novel with more stories that offer devilish comedy, eye-watering art, sad poetry, and bruised (but intact) innocence.

New York-based cartoonist Gabrielle Bell brings together thirty-five of the popular "Book of" series, plus several extra short comics, displaying the broad range of Bell's storytelling and cartooning talent. Her fiction includes "Book of Black," a story of Kate, a pretty young rhinoplasty assistant who encounters happy-go-lucky street people, a lascivious landlord, vapid co-workers, and Trent Reznor on her descent into madness. Bell's autobiographical tales feature the author as an eccentric old lady, a five hundred-foot-tall woman, in England, in Mexico with a baby, and being charmed and hypnotized by colorful San Francisco characters.

volume.name: When I'm Old and Other Stories

description: This is the story of two old friends who are reunited for one night, and wander together through a surreal, vaguely apocalyptic landscape, pondering life, griping about their circumstances, and trying to connect. Along the way they explore the nature of dreams, the fragile facade of civilization, and the tenderness of a true friendship.

Meet Jake: a man whose troubled past and bad luck have put him on the very bottom level of Gotham City. Once filled with good intentions, the former security guard is now haunted by his actions in the service of Bruce Wayne's rival, Derek Powers. And things are about to get worse.
name: Legends of the Dark Knight: Jake, Part 1

description: Batman: The Return, Batman, Inc. #1, Batman, Inc. #2, Batman, Inc. #3, Batman, Inc. #4, Batman, Inc. #5, Batman, Inc. #6, Batman, Inc. #7, Batman, Inc. #8, Batman Incorporated: Leviathan Strikes

The third Best of Dan DeCarlo volume continues in the tradition of Volumes one and two, collecting beautiful, vintage stories by DeCarlo Showcasing his numerous artistic skills. If Jack Kirby was the King of comics then Dan DeCarlo was the Emperor of Archie-and when you read this volume you'll understand why!
name: Volume 3

volume.name: Archie: The Best of Dan DeCarlo

description:
The New York Times bestselling author's Carpathian classic goes Manga!

Christine Feehan has reinvented the vampire novel with her New York Times bestselling Carpathian series. Now she and Berkley take her "out-of-the- ordinary" (Booklist) in a thrilling new direction--and this time it's more graphic than ever.

Riordan is an immortal Carpathian male, trapped and caged, his honor compromised by his captors. They're in his mind. They're in his blood. And not one can withstand his desire for revenge.

Juliette is an activist devoted to liberating animals from a secret jungle lab. What she stumbles upon is a prisoner like no other. She will release him from his bonds. He will release her from her inhibitions.

Another Horror House beauty, this collects three stories from the little-known classic series done in the late days of Fiction House Comics, Dr. Drew. Drawn by one-time Spirit assistant Jerry Grandenetti, the cloaked psychic investigator stalks through adventures that are rendered more Eisnerish than an actual Will Eisner story! Thrill to “The Devil’s Violin”, (from Rangers #50, 1949) “Sabina The Sorceress”, (from Rangers #56, 1950) and “The Strange Case Of The Absent Floor”. ( from Rangers #47, 1949) This is good stuff- spooky stories with personality, character, drama, humor asnd great design. Highly recommended. Color cover by Black and Grandenetti, interiors are black and white with graytones. Standard comic book format.

volume.name: Diary of a Mosquito Abatement Man

description: This issue consists of a hand painted figurine and a magazine on the issues featured character.
name: Metallo

description:
Award-winning crime novelist JASON STARR brings his unique vision to the Punisher!

A massive debt, a gun with untraceable bullets, one unthinkable choice.

Who’s side will the Punisher take?
name: Jimmy's Collision

volume.name: Untold Tales of the Punisher Max
